Ingredients:

For the brownie:
1 teaspoon flour
1/8 teaspoon cocoa powder
1/8 teaspoon baking soda
Pinch salt
1/2 teaspoon butter
1/4 teaspoon sugar
1/2 teaspoon water
5 mini chocolate chips
Dash vanilla
1/4 teaspoon egg, beaten
To finish:
1 tablespoon strawberry ice cream
1 tablespoon meringue

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

2. In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside.

3. In a saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water. Bring to a simmer, and stir in chocolate chips and vanilla. Cool slightly. Add wet ingredients to dry and add the beaten egg. Stir to combine, and pour into baking dish. Bake for 8 minutes. Allow to cool.

4. Trim brownie to fit into a small bowl. Line the bowl with plastic wrap and fill with strawberry ice cream. Top with brownie and freeze until hardened.

5. Remove from freezer and turn out onto a plate. Top with meringue and toast with a kitchen lighter until browned.

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon ground beef
1/4 teaspoon minced onion
1/4 teaspoon minced carrot
1/8 teaspoon minced garlic
1/8 teaspoon minced parsley
Dash of Worcestershire
Dash of ketchup, plus more for topping
Dash of Dijon
1/4 teaspoon egg
1/4 teaspoon breadcrumbs
Mashed potatoes, for serving

Steps:

1. In a small bowl, combine all ingredients. Form into a meatloaf, and spread more ketchup on top. Shape and bake at 400 degrees for 6 minutes.

2. Slice and serve with mashed potatoes.

2 (1/2-inch) slices rye bread
1/4 teaspoon Russian dressing
Cheese
1/4 teaspoon sauerkraut
2 (1/2-inch) slices corned beef
Butter
1 tiny potato
Oil, for frying
1 tiny pickle

Steps:

1. Spread Russian dressing on bread and top with cheese, sauerkraut and corned beef.

2. Heat butter in pan and grill sandwich until golden brown on both sides.

3. To make chips:  Slice the potato very thinly. Heat oil in small pot.

4. Add chips and fry until golden brown. Serve sandwich with chips and a pickle.

Ingredients:

Broth:
1 1/2 tablespoons chicken broth
1/4 inch piece ginger
1/4 teaspoon soy sauce
Wontons:
1 teaspoon ground pork
1/8 teaspoon soy sauce
1/4 teaspoon chives
1/8 teaspoon rice vinegar
1/4 teaspoon cornstarch
1/4 teaspoon grated ginger
Pinch crushed red pepper flakes
3 tiny wonton wrappers
Green onions, to garnish

Steps:

1. In a pot, heat all broth ingredients.

2. In a bowl, combine ground pork, soy sauce, chives, rice vinegar, cornstarch, grated ginger and red pepper flakes. Place a tiny pinch of pork mixture in the center of each wonton. Paint one corner with water and fold another corner on top of it. Place in broth and simmer for 4 minutes. Garnish with chives.

Persian cucumber slices, cut into triangles
Yogurt & dill spread
1-inch pieces of bread
1-inch pieces smoked salmon
Caviar
Radish slices, cut into triangles
1 tablespoon butter
Tiny scones
Whipped cream
A very small amount of jam

Steps:

4. Arrange tea sandwiches on a plate along with tiny scones, whipped cream and jam. Enjoy with your tea!

Salt and pepper
Pinch sugar
Dash apple cider vinegar
1/2 teaspoon sliced onion
1/8 teaspoon oil
Oil for frying

Ingredients:

For the brownie:
1 teaspoon flour
1/8 teaspoon cocoa powder
1/8 teaspoon baking soda
Pinch salt
1/2 teaspoon butter
1/4 teaspoon sugar
1/2 teaspoon water
5 mini chocolate chips
Dash vanilla
1/4 teaspoon egg, beaten
To finish:
1 tablespoon strawberry ice cream
1 tablespoon meringue

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

2. In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside.

3. In a saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water. Bring to a simmer, and stir in chocolate chips and vanilla. Cool slightly. Add wet ingredients to dry and add the beaten egg. Stir to combine, and pour into baking dish. Bake for 8 minutes. Allow to cool.

4. Trim brownie to fit into a small bowl. Line the bowl with plastic wrap and fill with strawberry ice cream. Top with brownie and freeze until hardened.

5. Remove from freezer and turn out onto a plate. Top with meringue and toast with a kitchen lighter until browned.

#TinyTuesday Spotlight:
Meet Betty!!✨ @bettystinyworld

“I started because I love hello kitty and miniatures but mostly the fact that I can create or “recreate” my most vivid memories of retro Sanrio times, basically I started doing anything that reminded me of my childhood and happy moments which is why I love to make cute things... I have two kids and I also take things they like such as the tiny video game shop. I make all the Mexican candy/snacks also with my favourites and from memories 🤗”

From Sanrio to a cute Mexican Candy Shop, we’re obsessed with all things tiny and wish we could shop at Betty’s tiny stores! Be sure to give ➡️ @bettystinyworld a follow and check out her DIY tutorials!

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon ground beef
1/4 teaspoon minced onion
1/4 teaspoon minced carrot
1/8 teaspoon minced garlic
1/8 teaspoon minced parsley
Dash of Worcestershire
Dash of ketchup, plus more for topping
Dash of Dijon
1/4 teaspoon egg
1/4 teaspoon breadcrumbs
Mashed potatoes, for serving

Steps:

1. In a small bowl, combine all ingredients. Form into a meatloaf, and spread more ketchup on top. Shape and bake at 400 degrees for 6 minutes.

2. Slice and serve with mashed potatoes.

node.text:
#TinyTuesday Spotlight✨ Meet Akın Tek @miniceramicsart 

Akın Tek is a self-taught mini ceramics artist, working on a mini throwing wheel he designed and made himself. After 20 years of experience as an academic on critical reading and writing, he quit academia and turned his lifelong hobby to @miniceramicsart.

Tek believes that we grown-ups always cast a dull gaze on everything we get to see. We take them for granted, all is set and standardized for us. However, when scales shift, we find that our minds shift, too. This brings back our sense of astonishment and we see things anew. We care for and connect them as we did in our childhood, where almost everything has a tint of miracle.

“Ceramic artist @defnesamman was the first to encourage me to try my hand at mini ceramics. When I took my first tiny piece off the wheel, I remember that stupid smile on my face, made up of a sense of awe.  Since then, every single mini piece has given me and my followers that smile."

——————————————
Be sure to check out @miniceramicsart for more amazing creations and keep an eye out on our future recipes to see if you can spot any of Akın’s work that was so generously sent to us! ❤️
